# 🛰️ SLATE360 PLATFORM SYSTEMS CORE DESIGN CONTRACT

## 1. FILE SEGREGATION & LINE LIMIT RULES
- HARD ENFORCEMENT CEILING: Every single frontend UI view file, layout shell, canvas component, or data-client module created or refactored inside `app/`, `components/`, or `lib/` must remain strictly under **300 lines of code** to prevent tangled spaghetti code structures.
- If a component file approaches 250 lines, you must programmatically extract its logic into dedicated presentational leaf components, atomic custom hooks, or clean type configurations.

## 2. BRAND LOGO GEOMETRIC CONSTANTS
- The inline SVG asset inside `components/studio-ui/LogoProvider.tsx` must never use fluid inherited tracking layout tags, container flex boxes, or fluid padding constraints.
- Global Desktop Header Logo Target: Absolute layout anchoring (`absolute left-6 lg:left-12 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 shrink-0 z-50`). Sizing is locked: graphic icon matches `h-8 w-autoText text-[#00E699]`, font wordmark text typography is `text-2xl font-bold tracking-[0.15em] text-white ml-4`.
- Global Mobile View Header Logo Target: Fixed `h-6 w-auto block text-[#00E699]` with wordmark typography set cleanly to `text-lg font-bold tracking-[0.12em] text-white ml-2`.

## 3. DEVICE-ADAPTIVE RESPONSIVE FORK
- Desktop Monitors (>= 1024px Viewports): Implement an asymmetrical split layout grid mapping 55% Text Column Width and 45% Embedded Media Canvas Width. Enforce full snap scroll tracking container blocks (`lg:h-[100dvh] lg:snap-start lg:overflow-hidden`).
- Mobile Phone Screens (< 1024px Viewports): High-density full-viewport height clamps (`h-[100dvh]`, `h-screen`, `snap-start`) are STRICTLY BANNED on content-heavy blocks. Containers must automatically fork into standard fluid scrolling tracks (`w-full h-auto py-16 px-6 block relative bg-[#0B0F15]`). Content must cascade linearly down the page layout axis with generous padding separations to completely eliminate text clipping and overlap failures.

## 4. THE HIGH-CONTRAST MONOCHROME DESIGN TOKEN MATRIX
- Background Page Canvas Layer: Deep Solid Slate-Black `#0B0F15`
- Primary Interactive Accent Highlight: Cybernetic Krypton Teal `#00E699`
- High-Contrast Text Layer 1 (Headers): Pure Titanium White `#FFFFFF`
- High-Contrast Text Layer 2 (Body): Crisp Chalk White `#F8FAFC`
- Secondary Structural Muted Frame Color: Industrial Silver `#A3AED0`
- Anti-Pattern Alert: All background layout card outlines around features, dark button pill shapes (`rounded-full`), emoji bullet point elements, and early-2000s cartoon icons are permanently banned from the project tree. Feature lists must use a clean, borderless layout row using raw typography strings styled in `text-slate-200 text-base font-normal tracking-wide flex items-start gap-2`, accompanied exclusively by a sharp laser dot chevron accent indicator node: (`»`) cast in high-contrast teal (`text-[#00E699] drop-shadow-[0_0_8px_rgba(0,230,153,0.6)]`).

## 5. RE-ROUTING CANONICAL TARGET CORES
- Authenticated account entry routes must completely bypass legacy folder locations (`app/site-walk/page.tsx`). Validated logins must route traffic exclusively to our modern studio hub cockpit route at **`/app`** (`components/dashboard-v3/DashboardV3Shell.tsx`), rendering exactly two clean application launch tiles on a solid `#0B0F15` base background canvas.
